Generic footer navbox. Styled by the <code>.vr-navbox-*</code> classes in [[MediaWiki:Common.css]] (design tokens from [[MediaWiki:Citizen.css]]) — one visual language for all entity-class navboxes.

Place at the very bottom of the article, after See also / References and before categories. Separate list entries with <code>&amp;nbsp;•&amp;nbsp;</code>.

Example usage:
<pre>
{{Navbox
| title = [[Weapons]]
| group1 = Melee
| list1  = [[Sword]] • [[Axes]] • [[Mace]] • [[Spear]] • [[Greatsword]] • [[Reaper]] • [[Slashers]] • [[Twinblade]] • [[Whip]] • [[Claws]]
| group2 = Ranged
| list2  = [[Crossbow]] • [[Longbow]] • [[Daggers]] • [[Pistols]]
| below  = [[Weapon Skills]] • [[Legendary Artifact Weapons]]
}}
</pre>

Parameters: <code>title</code> (required), <code>above</code>, <code>group1</code>–<code>group8</code> (optional row labels), <code>list1</code>–<code>list8</code> (row content; a row renders only if its list is non-empty), <code>below</code>.
[[Category:Navbox templates| ]]
</noinclude>
